entry.def: A walk-on part in a play or film is a very small part which usually does not involve any speaking.

example.ex: He and his family have walk-on parts in the latest film.
example.tran: 他和家人在最新的这部电影中有跑龙套的角色。

1. not capable of or especially not involving speech or spoken lines;
